  "prompt": "My girlfriend and I took a break. About two months later she told me she made out with her ex during our break. What do I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that you're going through such a challenging situation. Here are some steps you might consider:\n\n1. **Reflect on Your Feelings:** Take some time to understand how you feel about the situation. Are you hurt, angry, or confused? Knowing your emotions can help you communicate effectively.\n\n2. **Communicate Openly:** Have an honest conversation with your girlfriend about what happened. Ask her for any details you need in order to understand the context and her feelings during the break.\n\n3. **Assess the Relationship:** Consider whether this incident changes how you feel about your relationship. Is it something you can move past, or does it fundamentally alter your trust and connection?\n\n4. **Set Boundaries and Expectations:** Discuss what you both want from the relationship moving forward. Set clear boundaries and expectations to avoid similar issues in the future.\n\n5. **Seek Support:** Sometimes, it's helpful to talk to a trusted friend or counselor to gain perspective and support.\n\n6. **Make a Decision:** Based on your feelings, the conversation, and your assessment of the relationship, decide whether to continue the relationship or to move on.\n\nRemember, there\u2019s no right or wrong answer here\u2014what matters is what feels right for you both.",
